    {
        "content": "<p>You could state it like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CategoryTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Limits</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟶</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofHom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">castRingHom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟶</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≫</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≫</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsLimit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Fork</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofι</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h₀</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This constructs an explicit equalizer diagram <code>Fork.ofι i h₀</code> and claims that there is a contradiction if this diagram is limiting.</p>",
        "id": 505625523,
        "sender_full_name": "Markus Himmel",
        "timestamp": 1741944754
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Mathlib also contains \"being an equalizer of something\" as <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=CategoryTheory.RegularMono#doc\">docs#CategoryTheory.RegularMono</a>, so another way of packaging it is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CategoryTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Limits</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟶</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RingCat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofHom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">castRingHom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">RegularMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 505626051,
        "sender_full_name": "Markus Himmel",
        "timestamp": 1741944899
    },
